# worktrunk core.bare repro transcript (2026-06-08)

Environment: wt v0.56.0, bash, /tmp/opencode/

## Control: normal repo (no core.bare flip)

```text
$ git init -b main repo && cd repo
$ git config commit.gpgsign false user.email=t@t.com user.name=T
$ echo hello > README.md && git add README.md && git commit -m init
$ git switch -c feat/v3
$ wt switch --create fix/repro --base main --no-hooks --yes
✓ Created branch fix/repro from main and worktree @ .../repo.fix-repro
$ echo change > ../repo.fix-repro/README.md
$ git -C ../repo.fix-repro commit -am 'fix: change'
$ cd ../repo.fix-repro && wt merge main --no-hooks --yes
✓ Merged to main (1 commit, 1 file, +1, -1)
◎ Removing fix/repro worktree & branch in background (same commit as main, _)
$ git -C ../repo config core.bare
false
```

## Trigger class: bare-at-.git + worktreeConfig

```text
$ git init --bare -b main myproject/.git
$ git --git-dir=myproject/.git config core.bare false
$ git --git-dir=myproject/.git config extensions.worktreeConfig true
$ printf '[core]\n\tbare = true\n' > myproject/.git/config.worktree
$ git --git-dir=myproject/.git worktree add myproject/main main
$ cd myproject/main && git switch -c feat/v3
$ wt switch --create fix/repro --base main --no-hooks --yes
▲ Bare repo at myproject/.git — worktrees will be at myproject/.git.fix-repro
✓ Created branch fix/repro ... @ myproject/.git.fix-repro
$ cd myproject/.git.fix-repro && wt merge main --no-hooks --yes
✓ Merged to main (1 commit, 1 file, +1, -1)
◎ Removing fix/repro worktree & branch in background (same commit as main, _)
○ Switched to worktree for main @ myproject/.git
$ grep bare myproject/.git/config
	bare = false
$ cat myproject/.git/config.worktree
[core]
	bare = true
```

Shared config stayed `bare = false`; effective `git config core.bare` reads `true` via config.worktree merge.
Agentera incident reported shared `.git/config` poisoned to `core.bare = true` (stricter breakage).
